2026-03-01 | Minimum Number of Deci-Binary Numbers

	Question
Given decimal string n,
return the minimum number of deci-binary numbers
required to sum up to n.

	Approach
1.	Traverse each character of n.
2.	Convert it to integer.
3.	Track the maximum digit.
4.	Return that maximum.
5.	Time Complexity:
		O(length of n)
6.	Space Complexity:
		O(1)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    int minPartitions(string n) {
        int maxDigit = 0;

        for (char c : n) {
            maxDigit = max(maxDigit, c - '0');
        }

        return maxDigit;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Each deci-binary number can contribute
at most 1 per digit position.
So the largest digit determines
the minimum number of deci-binary numbers needed.
